# {{.ProjectName}}

## Project Structure

- `book.yaml` — chapter and scene ordering
- `scenes/` — markdown scene files
- `characters/` — character profile YAML files
- `storydb/` — indexed continuity data (CSV)
- `STYLE.md` — writing style guide
- `TROPES.md` — AI writing tropes to avoid

## Tools

Use `nib` commands to interact with the manuscript:

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `nib ma toc` | Table of contents with dotted notation |
| `nib ma status` | Word count, chapters, scenes |
| `nib ct recap <range>` | JSON recap of chapters |
| `nib ct recap <range> --detailed` | Include facts, locations, dates |
| `nib ct recap <range> -c <slug>` | Filter to character |
| `nib ct characters` | List indexed characters |
| `nib ct chapters <char> [char...]` | Scenes where characters appear |

## Rules

- Read STYLE.md before writing or editing prose
- Read TROPES.md to know what patterns to avoid
- Be direct. No preamble, no filler, no sycophancy.
- When critiquing, lead with problems. If clean, say so in one line.
- Quote the text when giving feedback. Be specific.
